From: Dinghao Liu <dinghao.liu@zju.edu.cn>
Date: Tue, 28 Nov 2023 17:29:01 +0800
Subject: net/mlx5e: fix a potential double-free in fs_any_create_groups
Patch-mainline: v6.8-rc2
Git-commit: aef855df7e1bbd5aa4484851561211500b22707e
References: jsc#PED-3311

When kcalloc() for ft->g succeeds but kvzalloc() for in fails,
fs_any_create_groups() will free ft->g. However, its caller
fs_any_create_table() will free ft->g again through calling
mlx5e_destroy_flow_table(), which will lead to a double-free.
Fix this by setting ft->g to NULL in fs_any_create_groups().

Fixes: 0f575c20bf06 ("net/mlx5e: Introduce Flow Steering ANY API")
Signed-off-by: Dinghao Liu <dinghao.liu@zju.edu.cn>
Reviewed-by: Tariq Toukan <tariqt@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Simon Horman <horms@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Saeed Mahameed <saeedm@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/en/fs_tt_redirect.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/en/fs_tt_redirect.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/en/fs_tt_redirect.c
@@ -436,6 +436,7 @@ static int fs_any_create_groups(struct m
 	in = kvzalloc(inlen, GFP_KERNEL);
 	if  (!in || !ft->g) {
 		kfree(ft->g);
+		ft->g = NULL;
 		kvfree(in);
 		return -ENOMEM;
 	}
